> The darkness before Dawn is lithe, live,<br>
> And as it coils, it circumscribes sight,<br>
> sealing a small world without others.<br>
> And one feels wrapped in this world,<br>
> warm (no matter the weather),<br>
> And forget their fears - by humans forlorn.<br>

> Because we are porcupines, poking each other<br>
> And though we want to walk together,<br>
> Always our shadow shows behind us<br>
> And from our hearts fear has not fled.<br>
> It reminds us to remain on guard,<br>
> And includes our intimate friends as<br>
> Eternal enemies whose shadows are strange,<br>
> And not ours.
